It reported a general decline in citizens' participation, human rights, rule of law and security on the continent - which were worsened by the impact of Covid-19. 2019's score on governance fell by 0.2 points below that of 2018 but progress has been slowing since 2015. "This is a testing time for Africa...Citizensâ€™ dissatisfaction and mistrust with governance delivery are growing. African states have an opportunity to demonstrate both their resolve to safeguard democracy and their ability to drive a new growth model," said the foundation's Chair, Mo Ibrahim. Nevertheless, the researchers found that a majority of Africans live in a country where governance is better than it was a decade ago. --BBC--